THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 277A of NRS is hereby amended by
2 adding thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. In a county whose population is 100,000 or more, a
4 commission shall:
5 (a) Install and maintain appropriate infrastructure and
6 technology designed to mitigate safety risks to transit operators,
7 including, without limitation, the use of:
8 (1) Barriers to restrict the unwanted entry of passengers
9 and unauthorized persons and objects into the workstation of a
10 transit operator; and
11 (2) Panic buttons and other technology designed to mitigate
12 safety risks to transit operators.
13 (b) Install and maintain appropriate signage informing the
14 public about the criminal penalties for crimes committed against
15 transit operators or the public, including, without limitation, the
16 criminal penalties for:
17 (1) Assault of a transit operator pursuant to NRS 200.471;
18 (2) Battery of a transit operator pursuant to NRS 200.481;
19 and
20 (3) Violation of a public transportation trespass order
21 pursuant to section 2 of this act.
22 2. As used in this section, “transit operator” has the meaning
23 ascribed to it in NRS 200.471.
24 Sec. 2. Chapter 200 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
25 thereto a new section to read as follows:
26 1. If a person is convicted of a violation of NRS 200.471 or
27 200.481 committed upon a transit operator, the governmental
28 entity operating the public mass transportation system for which
29 the transit operator was performing his or her duties may petition
30 the district court in the county in which the violation occurred
31 for the issuance of a public transportation trespass order pursuant
32 to this section.
