1 Within 30 days after a petition for modification or termination of
2 an order is filed pursuant to this section, the court shall hold a
3 hearing to determine whether to modify or terminate the order.
4 The governmental entity that filed the petition for the order is
5 entitled to notice of the hearing and an opportunity to be heard at
6 the hearing. If the court finds, by a preponderance of the evidence,
7 that modification or termination of the order is warranted and
8 would not jeopardize public safety or transit operations, the court
9 may modify or terminate the order.
10 9. A governmental entity that operates a public mass
11 transportation system shall:
12 (a) Maintain records of any public transportation trespass
13 order issued pursuant to this section; and
14 (b) Periodically review those records to ensure proportionality
15 and fairness.
16 10. A governmental entity that operates a public mass
17 transportation system which has obtained a public transportation
18 trespass order pursuant to this section may file a petition to
19 terminate or modify the order. Upon the filing of such a petition,
20 the court shall modify or terminate the order as requested in the
21 petition.
